<item>
            <title>[HIVE-3839] adding .gitattributes file for normalizing line endings during cross platform development</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-3839</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On the lines of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8912&quot; title=&quot;adding .gitattributes file to prevent CRLF and LF mismatches for source and text files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-8912&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-8912&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; .&lt;br/&gt;
Many developers clone the apache/hive git repository to make changes.&lt;br/&gt;
Adding a .gitattributes file will help in doing the right thing while checking out files on Windows (eg- adding \r\n on checkout of most text files, preserving \n in case of *.sh files ), and replacing \r\n with \n while checking in code back into a git repository.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
